What happens when you initialize a repository? Why do you need to do it?

How is the staging area different from the working directory and the repository?
What value do you think it offers?

The staging area is a middle path that lies between the working directory and repository. It allows us to put multiple files in a single commit to later send it to the repository. In a nutshell staging area makes things easy for the repository. 

